Elevate your career in law enforcement technology and join us to make
Queensland the safest state – apply now and make a real impact!

** The core capability requirements for this role are: **

  * Contribute to all stages of the software development process including designing, coding, reviewing, testing, correcting and documenting complex system components from supplied specifications using agreed standards and tools to achieve a well-engineered result. 
  * Assist with defining the technical criteria for product / component selection and contribute to decisions about tools, methods and approaches. 
  * Provide advice on business system solutions, products and services to internal and external stakeholders 
  * Identify and participate in self-development opportunities in the field application and web service development. 
  * Work collaboratively to deliver timely client focused support of applications in a 24/7 operational environment. 

** Role Requirements: **

_ ** Qualification: ** _

  * A tertiary level qualification in Information Technology, Computer Science or equivalent is highly desirable 

_ ** Technical/ Operational/ Educational experience: ** _

** Demonstrated use and skill with the following technologies: **

  * Microsoft.NET Framework/Core (C#) 
  * Java 
  * Microsoft Design Patterns (MVC, MVVM, Razor) 
  * Microsoft Visual Studio 2022 
  * Azure DevOps, TeamCity, DevOps 
  * Testing Frameworks (MSTest, NUnit, Gherkin, SpecFlow) 
  * Entity Framework / Dapper / SQL 
  * Microsoft Web Services technologies 
  * Strong knowledge in all phases of the System Development Lifecycle (SDLC) 

_ ** Other Desirable Experiences: ** _

  * Knowledge of developing within a Secure Software Development Lifecycle 
  * Demonstrated experience in Cross Functional Agile teams 
  * Knowledge of Java development technologies 
  * Knowledge of Microsoft Web Platform 

_ ** SFIA Skills: ** _

The following technical criteria reflect relevant professional skills and
competencies from the Skills Framework for the Information Age (SFIA)
Framework relevant to this role:

  * Level: 3 
  * Skill Code(s) 
  * PROG: Programming/software development 

